Installation Instructions for iota

Prerequisites

Before installing, make sure you have the following tools and libraries:

- GCC or another compatible C/C++ compiler
- Make

Building from Source

1. Configure iota:
   ./configure [OPTIONS]
   To see a list of available options, run:
   ./configure --help

2. Compile iota:
   make
   You can speed up compilation by using multiple jobs:
   make -j$(nproc)

3. Install iota:
   make install
   You may need superuser privileges:
   sudo make install

4. Verify the installation:
   iota --version

Uninstallation

To remove the installed files, run:
make uninstall

Cleaning Up

To clean up intermediate files:
make clean

To remove all generated files and configuration:
make distclean

Troubleshooting

If you encounter errors during configuration, make sure all dependencies are installed and up-to-date. You can check for missing libraries or tools in the output of the ./configure step.

For further assistance, please open an issue on the GitHub <https://github.com/vx-clutch/iota>.
